description:

Their name alone struck fear into the hearts of all other sailors! 
They were 'soul vanquishers'.

100% Cotton - 155 g/m² (4.65oz.)

Erano 'conquistatori di anime'.

name: 59 Club Father Bill
description:
Rev William Shergold, a biker priest who founded one of the world’s largest motorcycle clubs, died on 17 May, 2009, aged 89.

The 59 Club currently had over 30,000 members.
